1. Google's official WHOIS server is listed as "whois.markmonitor.com", which matches with a known legitimate registrant, MarkMonitor, Inc.
2. The creation date (`1997-09-15`) predates most cyber threats becoming prevalent in today's digital landscape.
3. The updated date (`2024-08-02`) indicates that the registration details have been recently verified or updated by the registrar.
4. The expiration date (`2028-09-13`) shows that this domain will remain under control until at least several years into the future.
5. All four types of prohibitions - client update, transfer, and delete - are present but do not necessarily indicate a malicious intent; they could simply mean the owner wants to maintain strict control over their domain.

However, please note that while the WHOIS data doesn't suggest immediate danger, further investigation may still be necessary before concluding definitively about the safety of a domain. Always verify multiple sources when assessing potential risks associated with domains.

2. The creation date (`1997-09-15`) predates most cyber threats becoming prevalent in today's digital landscape.
3. The updated date (`2024-08-02`) indicates that the registration details have been recently verified or updated by the registrar.
4. The expiration date (`2028-09-13`) shows that this domain will remain under control until at least several years into the future.
